author: cbc
title: 2 vehicle fires in Conception Bay North
text:
Two RCMP detachments were kept busy with vehicle fires over the last 24 hours in two communities half an hour away from each other.
Bay Roberts RCMP were called to a fire in Spaniard's Bay around 8:30 p.m. Wednesday.
That vehicle was reported stolen in St. John's, and the fire is considered suspicious.
Police say the fire, one of two overnight, is suspicious. (Submitted by Melissa Whalen-Simms)
Around 3:50 a.m. Thursday, police were called to a pickup on fire at a commuter parking lot in Mahers. The truck was destroyed.
The fire is still under investigation by the Holyrood RCMP and the cause has not yet been determined.
